User Manual
Risk Assessment
New Equipment -- Training currently under development
The X1 Series is a FDM printer that can print in a variety of plastics.
it is faster and more affordable than the Markforged printer
it can print multiple colours/similar materials in a single print by automatically switching between filaments with its single nozzle
Get Trained!
To use this equipment:
study training materials
get 100% on equipment quiz
get 100% on general safety quiz
attend a practical (check Meetup, email owners)
get marked as trained by a trainer
External Materials
Manually optimising where supports are placed
Reducing waste during multi material prints
Exhaustive tutorials on Bambu Slicer software
Please keep in mind that all the trainers at Makespace are volunteers. They, like all Makespace members, give their time to continually improve our community. Do not hesitate to ask for training, or indeed any questions, but please be patient as they make time in their schedules to run the practical assessments.

Please contact Makespace Management or the owners for any info.
